3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates ORDI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with no fee charged by Bitget. Funding rates are capped at ±0.75% to prevent extreme scenarios, though ORDI rarely approaches these limits. Bitget displays real-time predicted funding rates and historical data for the past 90 days."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ORDI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI represents the Bitcoin Ordinals ecosystem and often exhibits unique funding patterns independent of major cryptocurrencies, creating arbitrage opportunities. The token's relatively small market cap and association with Bitcoin NFTs leads to episodic volatility and corresponding funding rate spikes. Bitget's fast listing of emerging tokens like ORDI provides early access to funding rate strategies before other major exchanges."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI funding rates on Bitget have shown extreme volatility since listing, with rates frequently exceeding ±0.3% during market euphoria or panic phases. During the 2023 Bitcoin Ordinals hype cycle, ORDI sustained positive funding rates above 0.1% for extended periods as retail traders maintained leveraged long positions. The token exhibits seasonal patterns tied to Bitcoin network activity and NFT market cycles, with funding rates often spiking during periods of high Ordinals inscription activity. Weekend periods typically see reduced funding rate volatility as institutional interest wanes."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI's limited trading venues create significant funding rate arbitrage potential, particularly between Bitget and smaller exchanges that list BRC-20 tokens. The 8-hour funding cycle allows traders to capture rate differentials by maintaining opposite positions across exchanges, though this requires careful monitoring due to ORDI's price volatility. Cross-exchange arbitrage is most profitable during periods when Bitget's funding rates deviate significantly from competitor exchanges like OKX or Gate.io. Traders can also exploit funding rate mean reversion tendencies, as ORDI rates above ±0.2% historically correct within 24-48 hours."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI's association with Bitcoin Ordinals creates unique risks including regulatory uncertainty around NFTs and potential Bitcoin protocol changes affecting Ordinals functionality. The token's small market cap makes it susceptible to manipulation and sudden liquidity shortages that can amplify funding rate volatility beyond normal parameters. Bitget's relatively newer status in derivatives trading means less historical data for risk modeling compared to established exchanges, requiring more conservative position sizing. Traders must also consider the correlation between ORDI and Bitcoin price movements, which can intensify during market stress and reduce the effectiveness of traditional arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes ORDI funding rates unique on Bitget compared to other BTC ecosystem tokens?","answer":"ORDI funding rates exhibit higher volatility than other Bitcoin ecosystem tokens due to its status as the first BRC-20 token and smaller trading base. Bitget's early listing advantage means ORDI often shows different funding patterns compared to exchanges that listed it later, creating cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"How does Bitget's 8-hour funding cycle affect ORDI trading strategies?","answer":"The 8-hour cycle allows for three daily funding payments, enabling more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to exchanges with longer cycles. Traders can time entries around the 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC funding times to maximize rate capture, particularly during high volatility periods."},{"question":"What position sizes are recommended for ORDI funding rate arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"Due to ORDI's smaller market cap and occasional liquidity gaps, position sizes should be limited to avoid impacting the funding rate calculation. Conservative sizing at 1-2% of daily volume helps prevent adverse selection while still capturing meaningful funding rate differentials during volatile periods."},{"question":"How do Bitcoin network events affect ORDI funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"Bitcoin network congestion and Ordinals protocol developments directly impact ORDI sentiment and funding rates. During high inscription activity or Bitcoin NFT market rallies, ORDI funding rates often turn significantly positive as traders bet on continued momentum, creating short-side arbitrage opportunities."}]}]
